# Chief of Staff Agent — Setup & Activation Checklist

**AGENT_ID:** `chief_of_staff_agent`
**ROLE:** Chief of Staff — Operations Orchestrator
**Schedule:** Daily at 7:00 AM EST (12:00 UTC)

## What It Does

Every day at **7:00 AM EST**, the agent automatically:

1. Pulls all active tasks from 4 ClickUp lists (Revenue Critical, Active Build, PRD Needed, Blocked)
2. Checks GitHub Actions workflow statuses for the knowledge-base-nextra repo
3. Reviews Vercel deployment health
4. Queries Neon DB project list
5. Synthesizes a **1-page Chief of Staff briefing** via Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile)
6. Posts the briefing as a new page under the Notion daily log
7. Auto-creates ClickUp tasks for any blockers, overdue items, or paused Revenue Critical projects
8. **Mondays:** also creates a full cross-project weekly plan task in Active Build

**It will never let a project go on pause without creating a tracking task.**

## Files Deployed

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.github/workflows/chief-of-staff.yml` | GitHub Actions workflow (cron: daily 7am EST) |
| `.github/scripts/chief_of_staff.py` | Agent script (ClickUp + GitHub + Vercel + Neon + Groq → Notion) |

## Setup Status

### ✅ Already Done

- [x] `GROQ_API_KEY` secret set (Groq llama-3.3-70b)
- [x] Workflow runs daily at 12:00 UTC (7am EST)
- [x] GitHub Actions workflow file deployed
- [x] Agent script deployed and tested

### 🔧 Remaining Setup — Add These Secrets

Go to: **Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret**

| Secret | Where to get it | Required? |
|--------|----------------|-----------|
| `CLICKUP_API_TOKEN` | ClickUp → Settings → Apps → API Token | ✅ Required |
| `NOTION_API_TOKEN` | [notion.so/my-integrations](https://www.notion.so/my-integrations) → New Integration | ✅ Required |
| `NOTION_DAILY_LOG_PAGE_ID` | The Notion page ID where daily briefings will be posted | ✅ Required |
| `VERCEL_TOKEN` | Vercel → Settings → Tokens | Optional |
| `NEON_API_KEY` | [console.neon.tech](https://console.neon.tech) → Account → API Keys | Optional |

### Getting NOTION_DAILY_LOG_PAGE_ID

Open your Notion daily log page → copy the URL. The page ID is the last 32-char hex string:

```
https://notion.so/Your-Page-1a2b3c4d5e6f...
                              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ this part
```

### Connecting the Notion Integration

1. Go to [notion.so/my-integrations](https://www.notion.so/my-integrations), create an integration called `Chief of Staff Bot`
2. Copy the token → add as `NOTION_API_TOKEN` secret
3. Open your daily log Notion page → `...` menu → `Add connections` → select `Chief of Staff Bot`

